<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-20T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-20T11:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/1743: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-20T11:00:00-05:00">November 20, 1933—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. My 91, November 16, 4 p.m. House passed bill in third debate
                            yesterday with amendments making reconsideration by the Senate
                                necessary.<note n="48" xml:id="d219fn48">By telegram No. 93,
                                November 21, the Chargé informed the Department that “Senate passed
                                debt bill as amended by the House before adjournment of Congress
                                sine die today.” (821.51/1744)</note> Provisions discussed my 88 and
                            89 are less objectionable in altered form.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>